The paper focuses on text classification, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses network community detection, which is a method commonly used in social network analysis and graph theory, falling under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses machine learning models such as Support Vector Machines and Random Forests, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions TFIDF, which is a common technique in information retrieval, falling under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact on conversational intelligence systems, falling under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
